msgid ""
"Shouts and shots from a Winchester gun suddenly ring out in the middle of the night. You rush out to see what's going on and find the steamer up in arms. Some Pilgrims run up to you and excitedly tell you that they have shot the escaping prisoner. Just as he was about to go overboard. You find Mateso beside Kurtz's man, who is lying in a pool of blood.\n"
"The Director arrives on the scene and reproachfully says, \"I knew this would happen! Why would you want to keep that man here and put us all in danger? After what he and his kind did to us? We should have gotten rid of him before... And then how did he manage to... well, he's dead now. Right, everyone to their quarters!\""
msgstr ""
"De repente, en mitad de la noche, se oyen gritos y disparos de un Winchester. Corres a ver qué está pasando y encuentras el barco en plena agitación. Unos peregrinos corren hacia ti y te informan con entusiasmo que han matado al prisionero que intentaba escapar. Justo cuando estaba a punto de saltar por la borda, ves a Mateso junto al hombre de Kurtz, que yace en un charco de sangre.\n"
"El director aparece en la escena y dice con reproche: –Sabía que esto sucedería. ¿Por qué querrías mantener a ese hombre aquí y ponernos a todos en peligro? Después de lo que él y los suyos nos hicieron... Deberíamos habernos deshecho de él antes... ¿Y cómo se las arregló para...? Bueno, ya está muerto. Bien, ¡todos a sus camarotes!"

msgid "In your Campaign Log, record that <i>the prisoner died while trying to escape</i> and cross out <i>you have a prisoner on board.</i>"
msgstr "Anota en el registro de campaña que <i>el prisionero murió tratando de escapar</i> y tacha que <i>tenéis un prisionero a bordo</i>."

msgid "the prisoner died while trying to escape"
msgstr "el prisionero murió tratando de escapar."

msgid ""
"Suddenly, shouts ring out in the middle of the night. You rush out to see what's going on and find the steamer up in arms. Some Pilgrims come running to you and excitedly tell you that they have caught the escaped prisoner just as he was trying to get into a cabin next to yours.\n"
"The Director stands above you on the bridge and addresses all the crew members: \"It's okay, we caught that devil! We had to tie him up tighter, and I have posted two armed men outside his cabin. Everyone go back to your quarters!\""
msgstr ""
"De repente, se oyen gritos en mitad de la noche. Corres a ver qué está pasando y encuentras al barco sumido en el caos. Unos peregrinos se acercan corriendo hacia ti, llenos de entusiasmo, y te informan de que han capturado al prisionero fugado justo cuando intentaba entrar en una cabina contigua a la tuya.\n"
"El director, desde el puente, se dirige a la tripulación: –Está bien, hemos atrapado a ese diablo. Tuvimos que atarlo más fuerte y he puesto a dos hombres armados vigilando fuera de su cabina. ¡Todos, regresen a sus aposentos!"

msgid ""
"You enter your cabin, vaguely hoping to get some more rest before arriving - in just a few hours - at your destination. When you open the door, you see, incredulously, that your cabin has been turned upside down. Your brain struggles to process what you see, but you finally realize the obvious. Who else but the escaped prisoner could have done such a thing? You saw all the other crew members on deck just moments ago. A quick inspection of your belongings tells you that nothing has been taken from you, except for Kurtz's belongings which you found in his hiding place at the Central Station.\n"
"You think for a moment. The prisoner took a lot of risks during his escape. Not only did he not leave the ship immediately, but he also created a diversion in order to come and get a few letters and photos belonging to Kurtz.\n"
"You think back to the nighttime assault that happened a while ago. You had thought that the objective was to kill you, or at least to slow down your progress towards Kurtz. But in reality, there were not that many of them, and your losses were limited. What if their goal all along was to recover Kurtz's belongings? You try to remember what was in the documents, if there was anything worth taking such risks to retrieve, but to no avail. No matter, you are convinced, and you are now a little closer to understanding Kurtz's true intentions when you face him."
msgstr ""
"Entras en tu camarote, con la vaga esperanza de poder descansar un poco más antes de llegar, en apenas unas horas, a tu destino. Al abrir la puerta, te quedas incrédulo al ver que tu camarote ha sido completamente revuelto. Tu mente lucha por procesar lo que ves, pero pronto te das cuenta de lo evidente. ¿Quién más que el prisionero fugado podría haber hecho algo así? Hace un rato, viste a todos los demás miembros de la tripulación en cubierta. Al inspeccionar rápidamente tus pertenencias, descubres que nada te ha sido robado, excepto las cartas y fotografías de Kurtz que habías encontrado en la Estación Central.\n"
"Piensas un momento. El prisionero tomó grandes riesgos durante su escape. No solo no abandonó el barco inmediatamente, sino que creó una distracción para buscar esos documentos de Kurtz.\n"
"Recuerdas el asalto nocturno de hace poco. Pensabas que el objetivo era acabar contigo o, al menos, retrasar tu avance hacia Kurtz. Sin embargo, las pérdidas fueron menores de lo esperado. ¿Y si el verdadero objetivo desde el principio era recuperar las pertenencias de Kurtz? Intentas recordar si había algo en esos documentos que justificara tal esfuerzo, pero no logras precisarlo. Aun así, ahora estás un paso más cerca de entender las verdaderas intenciones de Kurtz cuando te enfrentes a él."

msgid "In your Campaign Log, cross out <i>you found Kurtz's personal belongings."
msgstr "En el registro de campaña tacha que <i>encontrasteis las pertenencias de Kurtz</i>."

msgid ""
"You do not immediately obey the Director and instead go to Mateso's side to examine the body. The old man smiles gently at you, then after checking that no one is watching, he slips an envelope containing documents into your hands.\n"
"\"Here,\" the medicine man whispers to you. \"He had this hidden on him. I thought it best to give it to you, rather than to the Director...\"\n"
"Hiding your surprise, you thank Mateso and hurry to your cabin to see what it is. You are surprised to find that it is Kurtz's belongings that you found in his hiding place at the Central Station. And indeed, the safe in your cabin where they were stored is open. Incredible as it may seem, the prisoner escaped without raising an alarm, broke into your quarters, and stole the documents.\n"
"You think for a moment. The prisoner died for a few letters and photos belonging to Kurtz, when he could have jumped overboard immediately after his escape.\n"
"You think back to the nighttime assault that happened a while ago. You had thought that the objective was to kill you, or at least to slow down your progress towards Kurtz. But in reality, there were not that many of them, and your losses were limited. What if their goal all along was to recover Kurtz's belongings?\n"
"You quickly scan the documents, looking for something worthy of risking one's life to retrieve. To no avail. No matter, you are convinced, and you are now a little closer to understanding Kurtz's true intentions when you face him."
msgstr ""
"No obedeces inmediatamente al director y, en cambio, te acercas a Mateso para examinar el cuerpo. El anciano te sonríe amablemente y, después de asegurarse de que nadie te está observando, te entrega un sobre con documentos.\n"
"–Toma –te susurra el curandero–, él tenía esto escondido encima. Pensé que sería mejor dártelo a ti en lugar de al director...\n"
"Ocultando tu sorpresa, le das las gracias a Mateso y te apresuras a tu camarote para revisar el contenido. Para tu asombro, descubres que se trata de las pertenencias de Kurtz, las mismas que habías encontrado en su escondite en la Estación Central. Y, efectivamente, la caja fuerte de tu camarote donde las guardaste está abierta. Increíblemente, el prisionero escapó sin alertar a nadie, entró en tu habitación y robó los documentos.\n"
"Piensa un momento. El prisionero perdió la vida por unas cuantas cartas y fotografías de Kurtz, cuando bien podría haber saltado por la borda después de su fuga.\n"
"Recuerdas el asalto nocturno que ocurrió no hace mucho. Habías pensado que el objetivo era acabar contigo, o al menos retrasar tu avance hacia Kurtz. Sin embargo, no fueron tantos los atacantes y tus pérdidas fueron mínimas. ¿Y si el verdadero propósito desde el inicio era recuperar las pertenencias de Kurtz?\n"
"Revisas los documentos rápidamente, buscando algo que justifique el riesgo de la vida del prisionero. Sin éxito. Pero no importa, ahora estás convencido de que estás un paso más cerca de entender las verdaderas intenciones de Kurtz cuando llegue el momento de enfrentarlo."
